4. Background
-------------
BridgePoint has been used for many years to model applications, execute them
in the Verifier and translate them into software for embedded (and other) 
targets.
 
The Generated C code from the Model Compiler needs to be MISRA compliant.

MISRA C is a software development standard for the C programming language
developed by MISRA (Motor Industry Software Reliability Association).
Its aims are to facilitate code safety, portability and reliability in the
context of embedded systems, specifically those systems programmed in ISO C.

5. Analysis
-----------
5.1      Content Requirements
5.1.1    The C code generated by MC3020 model compiler should follow
         the MISRA rules
5.1.2    An implementation done for each rule to be applied on the
         generated C code shall be provided.

5.2      Assignments
5.2.1    MISRA-C Rule 13.1  (Maha)
5.2.2    MISRA-C Rule 13.3  (Heba)
5.2.3    MISRA-C Rule 14.10 (Heba ,Maha)     
6. Design
